I have thousands of grey beards

26
00:00:31.630 --> 00:00:32.995
I have thousands of grey beards.

27
00:00:32.999 --> 00:00:34.964
If your greybeards can fight
the queen will have them.

28
00:00:34.968 --> 00:00:38.768
They will fight hard.
like northerners.

29
00:00:43.843 --> 00:00:46.942
Our victory depends on the
efforts of the small folk.

30
00:00:46.946 --> 00:00:49.516
The King has promised
us some money.

31
00:00:49.682 --> 00:00:51.447
Did he say when?

32
00:00:51.451 --> 00:00:54.950
I've decided to
send Joffrey to Ward

33
00:00:54.954 --> 00:00:56.956
with my cousin Lady Jane Eryn.

34
00:00:57.190 --> 00:00:59.059
Aegon and Viserys
will accompany him.

35
00:00:59.192 --> 00:01:01.194
I need you to be the mother
to them that I can not.

36
00:01:01.361 --> 00:01:04.030
Guard them like a
dragon guards her eggs.

37
00:01:04.197 --> 00:01:10.170
Do you accept me as your queen
and ruler or do you cling even

38
00:01:10.370 --> 00:01:12.272
now to what you think you lost?

39
00:01:12.372 --> 00:01:14.507
You didn't come here after
quarrelling with your wife.

40
00:01:14.707 --> 00:01:17.977
Does it please you that her
legitimacy is contested as you

41
00:01:18.211 --> 00:01:21.748
stand here with a
castle and a dragon?

42
00:01:21.881 --> 00:01:24.451
Ser Winter Blackwood of
House Blackwood. Your Grace.

43
00:01:24.551 --> 00:01:27.353
Once you and your dragon
brings the queen's justice to

44
00:01:27.554 --> 00:01:29.985
the Brackens our
armies will be yours.

45
00:01:32.158 --> 00:01:34.090
Cole is already
preparing his attack.

46
00:01:34.094 --> 00:01:38.160
The two of you have been
plotting without my authority.

47
00:01:38.164 --> 00:01:40.200
They don't care what I think.

48
00:01:40.400 --> 00:01:42.998
Do you think that simply wearing
the crown gives you wisdom?

49
00:01:47.740 --> 00:01:49.109
Cole marches on Rook's Rest.

50
00:01:49.242 --> 00:01:50.239
Send me.

51
00:01:50.243 --> 00:01:51.507
No.

52
00:01:51.511 --> 00:01:54.009
You must send me. Your Grace.

53
00:01:54.013 --> 00:01:55.815
This was your secret plot. Cole?

54
00:01:55.915 --> 00:01:58.051
For the King himself
to lay ambush

55
00:01:58.251 --> 00:01:59.752
and mayhaps die in the attempt?

56
00:01:59.919 --> 00:02:01.154
No!

57
00:02:03.089 --> 00:02:04.324
Thanks the Gods!

58
00:02:04.424 --> 00:02:05.658
Dracarus!

59
00:02:16.436 --> 00:02:18.067
Where's his Grace?

60
00:05:36.803 --> 00:05:39.535
- Only one.
- That's enough. stand back.

61
00:05:46.546 --> 00:05:48.047
Behold!

62
00:05:48.614 --> 00:05:51.714
The traitor dragon Meleys!

63
00:05:51.718 --> 00:05:55.884
Slain at Rook's Rest

64
00:05:55.888 --> 00:05:57.690
by your king!

65
00:05:59.726 --> 00:06:01.256
To Aegon!

66
00:06:09.869 --> 00:06:13.102
- It can't be...
- They killed a dragon!

67
00:06:13.106 --> 00:06:16.209
Mark my words. this
is a black omen.

68
00:06:33.793 --> 00:06:36.496
Rhaenyra will answer this.

69
00:06:37.430 --> 00:06:39.098
'Tis an abomination.

70
00:06:40.133 --> 00:06:42.568
Don't they realize
we won the battle?

71
00:06:43.469 --> 00:06:45.605
Strange victory...

72
00:06:46.406 --> 00:06:48.036
if it was one.

73
00:07:05.224 --> 00:07:07.627
Behold!

74
00:07:08.861 --> 00:07:11.527
The traitor dragon Meleys!

75
00:07:11.531 --> 00:07:13.262
I thought the dragons was gods.

76
00:07:13.266 --> 00:07:16.865
Slain at Rook's
Rest by your king!

77
00:07:25.211 --> 00:07:26.946
It's just meat.

78
00:09:46.519 --> 00:09:47.716
Is he alive?

79
00:09:47.720 --> 00:09:49.785
His Grace...

80
00:09:49.789 --> 00:09:52.758
remains with us. for the moment.

81
00:10:49.482 --> 00:10:50.779
Is my son going to die?

82
00:10:50.783 --> 00:10:52.618
I'm afraid I cannot say.

83
00:10:52.918 --> 00:10:56.184
Now. if you'll excuse me. Your Grace.
these next hours are most critical.

84
00:10:56.188 --> 00:10:57.556
Of course.

85
00:11:10.436 --> 00:11:12.104
Easy as you can.

86
00:11:32.024 --> 00:11:35.094
Someone will have to
rule in his stead.

87
00:11:58.317 --> 00:12:01.016
- What happened?
- We took the castle.

88
00:12:01.020 --> 00:12:03.656
At the cost of some 900 men.

89
00:12:05.424 --> 00:12:07.126
So I've heard.

90
00:12:08.694 --> 00:12:11.393
I left a meager garrison
behind to protect it

91
00:12:11.397 --> 00:12:13.829
and the king's dragon.

92
00:12:13.833 --> 00:12:16.331
Sunfyre was long in the dying.

93
00:12:16.335 --> 00:12:19.071
The king. Ser Criston.
what befell him?

94
00:12:22.541 --> 00:12:25.173
His Grace fought valiantly.

95
00:12:31.350 --> 00:12:32.581
And Aemond?

96
00:12:39.658 --> 00:12:41.827
What was his part in this?

97
00:12:45.564 --> 00:12:47.666
I could not say.

98
00:12:51.137 --> 00:12:54.870
Our largest dragon
has been killed.

99
00:12:54.874 --> 00:12:59.311
Criston Cole marches about
the Crownlands unchallenged.

100
00:12:59.779 --> 00:13:02.982
Duskendale and
Rook's Rest are gone.

101
00:13:04.183 --> 00:13:05.580
We still have no ground army

102
00:13:05.584 --> 00:13:08.583
but the one we hope
that Daemon will raise.

103
00:13:08.587 --> 00:13:12.988
He who has left us...
after some marital spat.

104
00:13:14.693 --> 00:13:17.129
Do you take issue
with me. Ser Alfred?

105
00:13:19.565 --> 00:13:21.863
My loyalty to you
is proven. my queen.

106
00:13:21.867 --> 00:13:23.999
Your loyalty. perhaps.

107
00:13:24.003 --> 00:13:26.902
but your willingness to give
me deference in a time of war.

108
00:13:26.906 --> 00:13:30.172
I could never doubt
your capability.

109
00:13:30.176 --> 00:13:32.978
or your quickness of mind.

110
00:13:34.146 --> 00:13:36.077
It is merely that
the gentler sex.

111
00:13:36.081 --> 00:13:38.446
heretofore. has
not been much privy

112
00:13:38.450 --> 00:13:41.416
to the strategies of battle.

113
00:13:41.420 --> 00:13:43.422
or their execution.

114
00:13:44.924 --> 00:13:46.655
There has been peace
in our lifetime.

115
00:13:46.659 --> 00:13:49.361
You've seen no more
battles than I have.

116
00:14:09.048 --> 00:14:11.613
Send to Maidenpool and
to Crackclaw Point.

117
00:14:11.617 --> 00:14:12.781
Let them man their garrisons

118
00:14:12.785 --> 00:14:14.349
and give them stores or weapons

119
00:14:14.353 --> 00:14:15.888
if they find them wanting.

120
00:14:17.056 --> 00:14:18.520
If Cole pursues his campaign.

121
00:14:18.524 --> 00:14:21.890
- our allies must be ready.
- We must answer Rook's Rest.

122
00:14:21.894 --> 00:14:24.125
- and Duskendale.
- They are lost already.

123
00:14:24.129 --> 00:14:26.661
But Vhagar is
depleted after such

124
00:14:26.665 --> 00:14:27.829
a hard-fought battle.

125
00:14:27.833 --> 00:14:29.164
If Aegon is dead...

126
00:14:29.168 --> 00:14:30.565
We will soon know it.

127
00:14:30.569 --> 00:14:32.500
'Twould be a victory
in name only.

128
00:14:32.504 --> 00:14:34.536
They will soon prop up
another in his stead.

129
00:14:34.540 --> 00:14:35.871
The time is ripe.

130
00:14:35.875 --> 00:14:37.272
If we can strike King's Landing

131
00:14:37.276 --> 00:14:38.773
before their dragon
is recovered...

132
00:14:38.777 --> 00:14:40.408
Then I myself must do it.

133
00:14:40.412 --> 00:14:44.045
My queen. you are the crown.
It is out of the question.

134
00:14:44.049 --> 00:14:46.648
What would you have me do?

135
00:15:07.206 --> 00:15:09.275
Jace?

136
00:15:11.510 --> 00:15:13.112
Where are you going?

137
00:15:14.480 --> 00:15:18.680
To Harrenhal. To
treat with Daemon.

138
00:15:18.684 --> 00:15:20.048
Rhaenys is fallen.

139
00:15:20.052 --> 00:15:21.983
He must affirm his
loyalty to my mother

140
00:15:21.987 --> 00:15:24.023
and report his standing.

141
00:15:26.725 --> 00:15:29.124
And you think you
will tame him...

142
00:15:29.128 --> 00:15:30.759
when the queen
herself could not?

143
00:15:30.763 --> 00:15:33.695
My mother gladly sends you away

144
00:15:33.699 --> 00:15:35.497
to scout. to fight.

145
00:15:35.501 --> 00:15:38.700
whilst I'm here being forced
to play the coddled princeling.

146
00:15:38.704 --> 00:15:43.004
- It's humiliating. Baela.
- She only protects you.

147
00:15:43.008 --> 00:15:44.439
You are the succession.

148
00:15:44.443 --> 00:15:48.614
Then I must be seen to act
for her claim and mine.

149
00:15:52.384 --> 00:15:54.887
I can sit still no longer.

150
00:15:57.423 --> 00:15:59.024
I must act.

151
00:16:06.565 --> 00:16:08.000
The Freys.

152
00:16:10.002 --> 00:16:12.500
They control the
crossing at the Twins.

153
00:16:12.504 --> 00:16:15.236
Cregan Stark's graybeards
are marching south.

154
00:16:15.240 --> 00:16:18.707
If his men had a direct
route into the Riverlands.

155
00:16:18.711 --> 00:16:20.746
we would not have to
wait for Daemon to act.

156
00:16:21.513 --> 00:16:24.245
I will treat with The
Freys to secure it.

157
00:16:24.249 --> 00:16:25.985
She will not like it.

158
00:16:26.518 --> 00:16:30.356
Then don't tell her.
Not until I'm away.

159
00:16:43.535 --> 00:16:46.701
{\an8}The hour is late and
my dragon is hungry.

160
00:16:46.705 --> 00:16:50.105
{\an8}You have no choice
but to submit.

161
00:16:50.109 --> 00:16:51.906
Our terms are
simple. Lord Bracken.

162
00:16:51.910 --> 00:16:55.677
Renounce the false
king Aegon as a usurper

163
00:16:55.681 --> 00:16:58.446
and bend the knee to me

164
00:16:58.450 --> 00:17:00.248
or your house burns.

165
00:17:00.252 --> 00:17:03.284
I would sooner be the
Lord of Bones and Cinders

166
00:17:03.288 --> 00:17:07.722
than bend my knee before some
heathen Blackwood cunt...

167
00:17:07.726 --> 00:17:09.457
and his hired dragon.

168
00:17:09.461 --> 00:17:10.959
The Brackens were a
people hatched out

169
00:17:10.963 --> 00:17:13.561
of the deepest of the
Seven Hells. Your Grace.

170
00:17:13.565 --> 00:17:14.963
It would be a kindness
to oblige them

171
00:17:14.967 --> 00:17:17.032
and send them back
whence they came.

172
00:17:17.036 --> 00:17:18.299
Did your brother's head

173
00:17:18.303 --> 00:17:20.873
keep on its way
back to you. Willem?

174
00:17:21.206 --> 00:17:23.004
I heard the maggots got to it.

175
00:17:23.008 --> 00:17:26.078
That is quite the
impression. Lord Bracken.

176
00:17:27.046 --> 00:17:29.214
But alas. not an answer.

177
00:17:38.957 --> 00:17:41.256
We choose fire.

178
00:17:51.036 --> 00:17:54.473
I did not think they
would be so eager to die.

179
00:17:55.274 --> 00:17:57.076
They made their choice.

180
00:17:57.376 --> 00:18:00.408
- You should've indulged them.
- I need them alive.

181
00:18:00.412 --> 00:18:03.382
I came here to raise
swords. not corpses.

182
00:18:03.949 --> 00:18:07.015
But now you see what my house
has known for generations.

183
00:18:07.019 --> 00:18:09.050
They are pigheaded.
intransigent...

184
00:18:09.054 --> 00:18:11.824
They would rather
burn than succumb.

185
00:18:15.461 --> 00:18:17.629
Exactly the kind of men I need.

186
00:18:19.631 --> 00:18:21.029
It may yet be possible. I think.

187
00:18:21.033 --> 00:18:23.098
for both of us to
achieve our ends.

188
00:18:23.102 --> 00:18:25.867
We have fought them
for an age and more.

189
00:18:25.871 --> 00:18:27.402
Then perhaps you could try

190
00:18:27.406 --> 00:18:29.842
less fighting and more...

191
00:18:33.412 --> 00:18:35.280
persuading.

192
00:18:36.115 --> 00:18:38.884
They are unyielding in battle.

193
00:18:45.624 --> 00:18:48.490
But every man has a weakness.

194
00:18:48.494 --> 00:18:50.963
You take my meaning. then.

195
00:18:54.299 --> 00:18:58.570
There are things the crown
itself must not been seen to do.

196
00:18:59.872 --> 00:19:01.536
Show them your worst.

197
00:19:01.540 --> 00:19:03.838
I am your servant. Your Grace.

198
00:19:24.997 --> 00:19:28.696
Over the centuries.
many and more armies

199
00:19:28.700 --> 00:19:32.004
have broken themselves
against my bloody gate.

200
00:19:36.208 --> 00:19:38.210
Are you listening?

201
00:19:39.144 --> 00:19:40.379
My lady.

202
00:19:40.913 --> 00:19:43.715
The Eyrie itself is impregnable.

203
00:19:45.851 --> 00:19:49.083
Unless. of course. we're
descended upon from the sky.

204
00:19:49.087 --> 00:19:51.853
You promised the Queen
Rhaenyra 15.000 swords...

205
00:19:51.857 --> 00:19:55.127
In return for
protection. A dragon.

206
00:19:56.795 --> 00:19:59.460
Then she has
exceeded your terms.

207
00:19:59.464 --> 00:20:00.832
She sent two.

208
00:20:01.433 --> 00:20:03.932
Both still wet from the egg.

209
00:20:05.504 --> 00:20:08.036
I have hunting hounds
that are more fearsome.

210
00:20:08.040 --> 00:20:10.475
They are dragons nonetheless.

211
00:20:10.943 --> 00:20:12.273
I do not recall you specifying

212
00:20:12.277 --> 00:20:14.042
the size of the beast
in your request.

213
00:20:14.046 --> 00:20:15.948
Will you goad me. child?

214
00:20:16.515 --> 00:20:19.551
When your bread and shelter
now depend on my pleasure?

215
00:20:21.186 --> 00:20:23.155
The dragons will grow...

216
00:20:24.189 --> 00:20:26.391
- in time.
- I don't have time.

217
00:20:28.093 --> 00:20:30.462
I mislike feeling powerless.

218
00:20:31.863 --> 00:20:33.332
So do I.

219
00:20:39.805 --> 00:20:41.736
This will be your chamber.

220
00:20:41.740 --> 00:20:43.942
I'll expect you at
supper this evening?

221
00:20:46.878 --> 00:20:51.116
My sympathies for the
death of your grandmother.

222
00:20:59.091 --> 00:21:01.990
The way they spoke at
my small council today.

223
00:21:01.994 --> 00:21:05.560
Do they hold you responsible
for Rhaenys and her dragon?

224
00:21:05.564 --> 00:21:07.366
I would rather they had.

225
00:21:07.833 --> 00:21:10.369
They speak around me. not to me.

226
00:21:11.036 --> 00:21:12.200
They would make me queen.

227
00:21:12.204 --> 00:21:14.535
but they wish to keep
me here. confined.

228
00:21:14.539 --> 00:21:17.142
They betray their own smallness.

229
00:21:17.709 --> 00:21:19.007
In truth. I cannot fault them.

230
00:21:19.011 --> 00:21:23.144
I am now the sovereign.
I cannot do as I please.

231
00:21:23.148 --> 00:21:26.014
And war has ever
been for men to make.

232
00:21:26.018 --> 00:21:29.450
You are your father's
chosen successor.

233
00:21:29.454 --> 00:21:31.786
He did not prepare me to fight.

234
00:21:31.790 --> 00:21:33.821
If I had been a son.

235
00:21:33.825 --> 00:21:37.496
a sword thrust into my hand
the moment I could walk.

236
00:21:38.030 --> 00:21:40.265
Instead. I was given
my father's cup...

237
00:21:40.832 --> 00:21:43.298
taught the name of
every lord and castle

238
00:21:43.302 --> 00:21:44.999
between Storm's
End and the Twins.

239
00:21:45.003 --> 00:21:48.173
but not the difference
between hilt and foible.

240
00:21:48.974 --> 00:21:50.709
And they know it.

241
00:21:52.044 --> 00:21:55.610
- And Daemon as well...
- Shall your evening meal be served here. Your Grace?

242
00:21:55.614 --> 00:21:57.416
Not now.

243
00:22:03.355 --> 00:22:05.090
Will you send to him?

244
00:22:06.325 --> 00:22:09.157
For too long. I have
looked to him for strength.

245
00:22:09.161 --> 00:22:11.392
If I must be supplicant
to my own husband.

246
00:22:11.396 --> 00:22:13.231
what does that make me?

247
00:22:16.702 --> 00:22:19.905
I do not know my part. Mysaria.

248
00:22:22.741 --> 00:22:25.577
The path I walk has
never been trod.

249
00:22:26.745 --> 00:22:30.349
Criston Cole made a mistake.

250
00:22:31.783 --> 00:22:36.050
Parading a dragon's head through
the streets like a prize of war.

251
00:22:36.054 --> 00:22:38.119
but the people see an ill omen.

252
00:22:38.123 --> 00:22:39.721
Yes. as do I.

253
00:22:39.725 --> 00:22:42.957
They are afraid.
bread is scarce.

254
00:22:42.961 --> 00:22:44.392
the king has fallen.

255
00:22:44.396 --> 00:22:46.994
they whisper to each other
that when Viserys lived.

256
00:22:46.998 --> 00:22:49.230
there was peace.

257
00:22:49.234 --> 00:22:52.033
But will whispers
tear down stone...

258
00:22:52.037 --> 00:22:53.601
or break shields?

259
00:22:53.605 --> 00:22:57.004
Do not underestimate
your subjects.

260
00:22:57.008 --> 00:22:58.740
They are a thousand-thousand

261
00:22:58.744 --> 00:23:00.441
living in the shadow
of the Red Keep

262
00:23:00.445 --> 00:23:03.081
and forgotten for too long.

263
00:23:03.715 --> 00:23:06.013
And you think they
will turn to me.

264
00:23:06.017 --> 00:23:10.489
To the discontented.
rumors are feed.

265
00:23:15.026 --> 00:23:16.795
Your Grace.

266
00:23:18.997 --> 00:23:23.435
What you cannot do.
let others do for you.

267
00:23:24.636 --> 00:23:27.902
There is more than one
way to fight a war.

268
00:23:50.061 --> 00:23:52.727
The thought of her
lying in a field.

269
00:23:52.731 --> 00:23:55.534
broken amongst her enemies.

270
00:24:05.911 --> 00:24:10.215
Did your grandmother ever tell you
of the night she claimed Meleys?

271
00:24:11.082 --> 00:24:13.151
She snuck into the Dragonpit.

272
00:24:13.752 --> 00:24:16.321
She knew that place
better than any Elder.

273
00:24:16.788 --> 00:24:18.990
They say she could
see in the dark.

274
00:24:20.492 --> 00:24:22.290
My father was furious.

275
00:24:22.294 --> 00:24:24.325
His own mother's dragon.

276
00:24:24.329 --> 00:24:25.793
the fastest beast ever known.

277
00:24:25.797 --> 00:24:27.829
and she'd have none of him.

278
00:24:27.833 --> 00:24:30.302
But bent her neck to Rhaenys.

279
00:24:31.269 --> 00:24:33.371
She was fierce...

280
00:24:34.573 --> 00:24:36.708
in love and in anger.

281
00:24:39.211 --> 00:24:43.048
She did not always
care for me. but...

282
00:24:44.583 --> 00:24:48.854
for what she gave me in
the end. I'm grateful.

283
00:24:54.626 --> 00:24:57.696
I wished I had known
her when she was young.

284
00:25:03.268 --> 00:25:07.606
You are very like
her in some ways.

285
00:25:10.175 --> 00:25:14.976
And with her gone... I
must rely on you. I think.

286
00:25:14.980 --> 00:25:17.745
Your Grace?

287
00:25:17.749 --> 00:25:20.452
Would you give this
to your grandsire?

288
00:25:32.030 --> 00:25:34.599
I do not wish to stand alone.

289
00:25:38.303 --> 00:25:40.138
Daemon.

290
00:25:44.843 --> 00:25:46.311
Daemon.

291
00:25:47.012 --> 00:25:49.814
You were always the strong one.

292
00:25:51.683 --> 00:25:54.452
The finest swordsman...

293
00:25:57.122 --> 00:25:59.891
the fearless dragon rider.

294
00:26:01.560 --> 00:26:05.459
{\an8}Your brother had great
love in his heart...

295
00:26:09.534 --> 00:26:12.003
...but he lacked
your constitution.

296
00:26:12.837 --> 00:26:15.574
Viserys was unsuited
for the crown...

297
00:26:18.610 --> 00:26:22.747
but you... Daemon. you
were made to wear it.

298
00:26:42.901 --> 00:26:46.104
If only you'd been born first.

299
00:26:47.272 --> 00:26:49.708
My favorite son.

300
00:26:55.914 --> 00:26:59.384
Is the duck not to your
liking. Your Grace?

301
00:27:04.322 --> 00:27:07.826
There's also goose.
if you'd prefer it.

302
00:27:09.494 --> 00:27:11.425
I like the goose. myself.

303
00:27:19.704 --> 00:27:21.135
Uh. I'm not hungry.

304
00:27:21.139 --> 00:27:23.471
I was saying. given
the rather dire news

305
00:27:23.475 --> 00:27:25.310
from Rook's Rest...

306
00:27:26.144 --> 00:27:30.311
it appears the winds have shifted and
each side has suffered great loss.

307
00:27:30.315 --> 00:27:33.818
and will be unsure
of what is to follow.

308
00:27:34.986 --> 00:27:37.952
A good time. then. for
a show of strength.

309
00:27:37.956 --> 00:27:39.186
I believe Willem Blackwood

310
00:27:39.190 --> 00:27:41.660
is bringing House
Bracken to heel.

311
00:27:42.994 --> 00:27:46.431
We must ready the castle
to receive a great host.

312
00:27:48.600 --> 00:27:50.398
You seem sure of this.

313
00:27:50.402 --> 00:27:53.234
All men may be led. Ser Simon.

314
00:27:53.238 --> 00:27:54.973
Even Rivermen.

315
00:27:55.874 --> 00:27:59.944
'Tis a matter of showing them
whom it behooves them to follow.

316
00:28:01.246 --> 00:28:03.415
How does the work here progress?

317
00:28:03.682 --> 00:28:07.515
Oh. um... we're drawing
water for the kitchens

318
00:28:07.519 --> 00:28:10.051
- and lighting the forges.
- Very well.

319
00:28:10.055 --> 00:28:12.553
That is merely the
beginning. of course.

320
00:28:12.557 --> 00:28:14.321
The roof alone
has needed tending

321
00:28:14.325 --> 00:28:15.389
since the reign of Aenys.

322
00:28:15.393 --> 00:28:16.757
And the storerooms.

323
00:28:16.761 --> 00:28:18.726
And...

324
00:28:18.730 --> 00:28:21.232
and the Wailing Tower.

325
00:28:21.766 --> 00:28:24.265
The bats have made the
corridors almost impassable

326
00:28:24.269 --> 00:28:26.538
with the quantity of their...

327
00:28:27.572 --> 00:28:29.074
Their shit.

328
00:28:31.209 --> 00:28:33.107
{\an8}I venture there are
smiths and armorers

329
00:28:33.111 --> 00:28:35.576
{\an8}to be found near
Nutton and Riverbend.

330
00:28:35.580 --> 00:28:37.712
{\an8}Well. send for them.
and levy the farmers

331
00:28:37.716 --> 00:28:39.784
from Antlers to High Heart.

332
00:28:40.051 --> 00:28:43.851
Task their huntsmen to
bring us meat and wood.

333
00:28:43.855 --> 00:28:46.654
Um. there is. of course.
the matter of payment.

334
00:28:48.359 --> 00:28:52.864
After the. the tragedy
that befell his father...

335
00:28:53.164 --> 00:28:58.966
Larys transferred his family's
wealth to King's Landing.

336
00:28:58.970 --> 00:29:01.435
Is there any gold
left in your coffers?

337
00:29:01.439 --> 00:29:06.244
Enough to keep this small
establishment you see fed and warm.

338
00:29:07.145 --> 00:29:08.646
Relatively.

339
00:29:11.149 --> 00:29:14.548
I... I rather thought.
Your Grace. as

340
00:29:14.552 --> 00:29:17.852
emissary to the Queen

341
00:29:17.856 --> 00:29:21.789
that p-perhaps she could
provide the necessary coin

342
00:29:21.793 --> 00:29:25.392
- if you could only write to her.
- No.

343
00:29:25.396 --> 00:29:27.532
Harrenhal is my command.

344
00:29:27.999 --> 00:29:30.835
I shall guarantee
the payment myself.

345
00:29:31.803 --> 00:29:33.605
Up. up.

346
00:29:36.474 --> 00:29:38.543
Very well. Your Grace.

347
00:29:38.943 --> 00:29:41.980
You should address
me as "my king."

348
00:29:42.380 --> 00:29:44.215
But you're the prince.

349
00:29:44.549 --> 00:29:46.714
What would you call the
husband of the queen?

350
00:29:46.718 --> 00:29:48.516
- Well. the king...
- There it is. then.

351
00:29:48.520 --> 00:29:50.088
...consort.

352
00:29:51.089 --> 00:29:53.992
That last bit seems
unnecessary. don't you think?

353
00:29:59.731 --> 00:30:01.796
The armor was Valyrian steel.

354
00:30:01.800 --> 00:30:06.137
but His Grace suffered grievous
burns over much of his body.

355
00:30:07.138 --> 00:30:08.969
He has many broken bones.

356
00:30:08.973 --> 00:30:12.373
I fear there are
more injuries within.

357
00:30:12.377 --> 00:30:14.546
injuries we cannot see.

358
00:30:15.947 --> 00:30:18.245
We are grateful for your works.

359
00:30:18.249 --> 00:30:19.417
Grand Maester.

360
00:30:20.451 --> 00:30:23.021
- Has he woken?
- No.

361
00:30:24.389 --> 00:30:28.989
I must admit. I'm not
sure he will ever wake.

362
00:30:28.993 --> 00:30:32.459
I have plied my crafts
to their fullest extents.

363
00:30:32.463 --> 00:30:36.701
Our king's fate lies
with the gods now.

364
00:30:47.245 --> 00:30:50.211
A king cannot rule in his sleep.

365
00:30:50.215 --> 00:30:52.584
The realm will have
noticed his absence.

366
00:30:53.151 --> 00:30:56.784
Let them hear of his great
deeds at Rook's Rest.

367
00:30:56.788 --> 00:30:59.720
But now we must name a
regent to take his place

368
00:30:59.724 --> 00:31:01.559
until he recovers...

369
00:31:03.828 --> 00:31:05.129
or does not.

370
00:31:06.664 --> 00:31:08.929
A wise strategy. Your Grace.

371
00:31:08.933 --> 00:31:10.664
A regency will assure the people

372
00:31:10.668 --> 00:31:13.304
of the stability of the crown.

373
00:31:15.840 --> 00:31:19.043
Did you have a candidate
in mind. Your Grace?

374
00:31:19.510 --> 00:31:21.275
I myself served in this
role for my husband.

375
00:31:21.279 --> 00:31:22.810
I am well-prepared
to do it again.

376
00:31:22.814 --> 00:31:24.345
You played your part admirably

377
00:31:24.349 --> 00:31:25.946
in a time of peace. Your Grace.

378
00:31:25.950 --> 00:31:28.549
but circumstances have changed.

379
00:31:28.553 --> 00:31:30.217
And here I had forgotten.

380
00:31:30.221 --> 00:31:32.453
The king does not
lack for heirs.

381
00:31:32.457 --> 00:31:37.424
The obvious choice is his
immediate successor. Prince Aemond.

382
00:31:37.428 --> 00:31:38.926
Agreed.

383
00:31:38.930 --> 00:31:41.795
Aemond is young.

384
00:31:41.799 --> 00:31:44.736
And his lack of restraint
has already cost us dearly.

385
00:31:53.978 --> 00:31:58.012
It is experience that offers
the surest path to security.

386
00:31:58.016 --> 00:32:01.215
Queen Alicent ably shouldered
the duties of the realm

387
00:32:01.219 --> 00:32:02.883
when her husband's
health failed him.

388
00:32:02.887 --> 00:32:04.251
Experience is valuable. yes.

389
00:32:04.255 --> 00:32:05.719
but the dowager
queen is a woman.

390
00:32:05.723 --> 00:32:08.923
I am no stranger to rule or
to sitting at this council.

391
00:32:08.927 --> 00:32:10.291
Aemond is a fearsome
dragon rider.

392
00:32:10.295 --> 00:32:11.725
His skill is best
employed in the field.

393
00:32:11.729 --> 00:32:14.595
but my experience is
needed here. at this table.

394
00:32:14.599 --> 00:32:16.997
No offense was meant.
Your Grace. but...

395
00:32:17.001 --> 00:32:22.303
- at a time when we must show strength.
- Lord Larys?

396
00:32:22.307 --> 00:32:24.943
I agree. Your Grace. It
must be Prince Aemond.

397
00:32:26.844 --> 00:32:29.276
What would it say if. in
response to Rhaenyra's crowning.

398
00:32:29.280 --> 00:32:31.716
we raised up a woman of our own?

399
00:32:34.352 --> 00:32:35.853
But. um...

400
00:32:37.355 --> 00:32:39.286
but the Hand speaks
for the king's voice.

401
00:32:39.290 --> 00:32:41.526
Ser Criston. what say you?

402
00:32:48.366 --> 00:32:50.735
Aemond is the next in line.

403
00:32:52.804 --> 00:32:54.339
It must be him.

404
00:32:58.743 --> 00:33:00.979
It's agreed then.

405
00:33:22.266 --> 00:33:24.736
What is our standing
in the Riverlands?

406
00:33:26.070 --> 00:33:28.736
Uh. the banners of House Tully

407
00:33:28.740 --> 00:33:30.971
are in disarray. Your Grace.

408
00:33:30.975 --> 00:33:32.206
Prince Daemon has little hope

409
00:33:32.210 --> 00:33:34.842
of fielding an army
of any size. for now.

410
00:33:36.347 --> 00:33:38.445
We would do well to send
word to young Oscar Tully.

411
00:33:38.449 --> 00:33:40.381
It's only a matter of time

412
00:33:40.385 --> 00:33:42.750
before he inherits his
grandsire's mantle.

413
00:33:42.754 --> 00:33:44.785
Tell me. Lord Strong.

414
00:33:44.789 --> 00:33:46.420
how I can trust the
counsel of a man

415
00:33:46.424 --> 00:33:48.055
who leaves the jewel
of the Riverlands

416
00:33:48.059 --> 00:33:50.728
to be plucked by our enemy?

417
00:33:54.198 --> 00:33:55.629
Your brother's host
can meet Daemon.

418
00:33:55.633 --> 00:33:57.064
He should quicken its pace

419
00:33:57.068 --> 00:33:58.065
and check the Rivermen

420
00:33:58.069 --> 00:33:59.666
while their banners
are in disarray.

421
00:33:59.670 --> 00:34:01.969
I shall send Lord
Jason encouragement.

422
00:34:01.973 --> 00:34:04.805
- What else?
- We might turn our attention

423
00:34:04.809 --> 00:34:07.241
to the smallfolk here
in King's Landing.

424
00:34:07.245 --> 00:34:09.877
They have grown weary of
the Sea Snake's blockade.

425
00:34:09.881 --> 00:34:12.046
So have we all.

426
00:34:12.050 --> 00:34:13.247
Many are fleeing the city.

427
00:34:13.251 --> 00:34:16.621
spreading word of
their fear and unrest.

428
00:34:16.954 --> 00:34:20.054
Mm. then let the
gates be closed.

429
00:34:22.060 --> 00:34:24.758
No one is to leave or enter.
save with our consent.

430
00:34:24.762 --> 00:34:27.799
Merchants. so forth.

431
00:34:31.803 --> 00:34:33.871
Go to your tasks.

432
00:34:34.605 --> 00:34:36.937
We shall meet again
at first light.

433
00:34:36.941 --> 00:34:41.079
Oh. and someone cut down
the fucking ratcatchers.

434
00:34:47.919 --> 00:34:50.354
The city's safe no longer.

435
00:34:52.090 --> 00:34:53.591
There is no food.

436
00:34:54.459 --> 00:34:56.390
Our neighbors are
stealing from each other.

437
00:34:56.394 --> 00:34:57.691
We must get out.

438
00:34:57.695 --> 00:34:59.626
{\an8}And where would you have us go?

439
00:34:59.630 --> 00:35:01.899
North. maybe? South?

440
00:35:02.500 --> 00:35:04.631
For all we know. every road
leads into the dragons' teeth.

441
00:35:04.635 --> 00:35:07.105
Like the one they carted
through the streets?

442
00:35:07.772 --> 00:35:12.043
You think Rhaenyra will let
such an affront go unchallenged?

443
00:35:14.979 --> 00:35:17.711
We should make for Tumbleton.

444
00:35:17.715 --> 00:35:19.713
My brother will have room.

445
00:35:19.717 --> 00:35:21.819
You would have me turn beggar?

446
00:35:27.725 --> 00:35:30.591
Are we not beggars already?

447
00:35:30.595 --> 00:35:32.359
Have you been paid
for those machines

448
00:35:32.363 --> 00:35:33.293
you were forced to build?

449
00:35:33.297 --> 00:35:34.962
The king has promised payment.

450
00:35:34.966 --> 00:35:38.035
The king has lied!

451
00:35:49.514 --> 00:35:51.415
By all means...

452
00:35:52.083 --> 00:35:55.720
stay and wait for his
empty promises. husband.

453
00:35:57.588 --> 00:36:00.658
With them. you can feed
the mouths of ghosts.

454
00:36:39.897 --> 00:36:41.866
Presumed you'd be here.

455
00:36:42.233 --> 00:36:45.069
Seeing faithfully to the
Prince Regent's commands.

456
00:36:45.636 --> 00:36:47.601
Aemond is the next in line.

457
00:36:47.605 --> 00:36:50.704
- It is the order of things.
- You know what he is...

458
00:36:50.708 --> 00:36:52.944
what he has somehow become.

459
00:36:55.613 --> 00:36:56.910
Has your loyalty faded?

460
00:36:56.914 --> 00:36:58.879
Or does it flourish
only at night

461
00:36:58.883 --> 00:37:01.886
and flee the
sunrise like a moth?

462
00:37:05.523 --> 00:37:06.987
What I saw at Rook's Rest...

463
00:37:06.991 --> 00:37:10.428
What? What did you see?

464
00:37:14.432 --> 00:37:16.567
Their armor melted.

465
00:37:18.102 --> 00:37:20.938
There were men walking.
They were on fire.

466
00:37:24.141 --> 00:37:26.577
We have given the
war to the dragons.

467
00:37:27.979 --> 00:37:29.780
A dragon rider should lead us.

468
00:37:33.985 --> 00:37:36.250
And what of justice.
of temperance?

469
00:37:36.254 --> 00:37:39.523
Or is strength now
to be our only god?

470
00:37:44.829 --> 00:37:46.964
So you cast me aside.

471
00:37:47.999 --> 00:37:50.134
Have I not spared you?

472
00:37:51.836 --> 00:37:55.673
What we must do
now is... terrible.

473
00:37:57.508 --> 00:37:59.477
Will you preside over it?

474
00:37:59.977 --> 00:38:03.881
- Is this who you are. Alicent?
- I did not ask to be spared.

475
00:38:07.118 --> 00:38:09.453
And I did not give you
leave to speak my name.

476
00:38:22.366 --> 00:38:24.298
Halt!

477
00:38:29.740 --> 00:38:31.042
Stay back!

478
00:38:32.643 --> 00:38:34.478
We've got to get out!

479
00:38:35.146 --> 00:38:36.847
Somebody get him!

480
00:38:37.481 --> 00:38:39.579
Stay back! No!

481
00:38:39.583 --> 00:38:41.882
Holdfast. hold fast!

482
00:38:41.886 --> 00:38:44.388
Stay back! Hold!

483
00:38:49.126 --> 00:38:50.361
Back!

484
00:38:51.295 --> 00:38:54.332
Disperse. disperse!

485
00:38:55.366 --> 00:38:57.698
By order of Aemond Targaryen.

486
00:38:57.702 --> 00:39:00.567
Prince Regent and
Protector of the Realm...

487
00:39:00.571 --> 00:39:03.036
- Aemond?
- Does he mean the king?

488
00:39:03.040 --> 00:39:05.405
- I don't know.
- You cannot keep us here!

489
00:39:05.409 --> 00:39:08.475
- You are ordered to return to your homes!
- We want meat!

490
00:39:08.479 --> 00:39:10.143
- Meat!
- Meat!

491
00:39:20.257 --> 00:39:21.892
Stay back!

492
00:39:29.533 --> 00:39:34.000
Our Lord Grover Tully has
not declared for Rhaenyra.

493
00:39:34.004 --> 00:39:36.236
It means death to bare
steel against your liege.

494
00:39:36.240 --> 00:39:38.709
as I'm sure my prince is aware.

495
00:39:40.077 --> 00:39:42.446
And against your queen?

496
00:39:44.615 --> 00:39:45.649
Hm?

497
00:39:49.253 --> 00:39:53.157
Jason Lannister is
marshaling to the west.

498
00:39:53.991 --> 00:39:56.327
We need to check him
before he reaches Riverrun.

499
00:39:57.128 --> 00:39:59.059
That requires passage.

500
00:39:59.063 --> 00:40:01.528
And if Stark's army is too slow?

501
00:40:01.532 --> 00:40:03.296
The wind's rising.

502
00:40:03.300 --> 00:40:04.931
Winter is nigh upon us.

503
00:40:04.935 --> 00:40:06.633
Our hesitance does not lie

504
00:40:06.637 --> 00:40:08.602
in Rhaenyra as Queen.

505
00:40:08.606 --> 00:40:12.973
nor in the ruminations
of Lord Tully. the oaf.

506
00:40:12.977 --> 00:40:15.909
Our fear lies in Vhagar.

507
00:40:15.913 --> 00:40:18.912
You fear a dragon leagues away

508
00:40:18.916 --> 00:40:21.681
when mine own sits
outside your walls?

509
00:40:25.856 --> 00:40:29.427
- Do you offer us your protection?
- I do.

510
00:40:35.866 --> 00:40:38.932
And the protection of my uncle.

511
00:40:38.936 --> 00:40:43.236
And Daemon. I'm sure.
has consented to this?

512
00:40:43.240 --> 00:40:45.338
He will do as his
queen commands.

513
00:40:45.342 --> 00:40:47.307
That does lend us some comfort.

514
00:40:47.311 --> 00:40:48.708
Though it occurs
to me that dragons

515
00:40:48.712 --> 00:40:52.283
- cannot be in two places at once.
- Or three.

516
00:40:55.119 --> 00:40:57.054
What do you want?

517
00:40:59.123 --> 00:41:03.056
Larys Strong has been
relieved of his castle.

518
00:41:03.060 --> 00:41:06.397
Does the queen intend
to raise up a new lord?

519
00:41:10.734 --> 00:41:12.303
You want Harrenhal.

520
00:41:30.955 --> 00:41:36.160
For that... my mother will
want more than your crossing.

521
00:41:37.761 --> 00:41:39.930
What does Her Grace desire?

522
00:41:42.466 --> 00:41:44.768
Bent knees.

523
00:42:38.522 --> 00:42:39.757
Up.

524
00:42:40.291 --> 00:42:42.055
You were born to wield a sword.

525
00:42:42.059 --> 00:42:46.192
but not so much an axe. perhaps.

526
00:42:46.196 --> 00:42:47.861
There are others
who would sit idle

527
00:42:47.865 --> 00:42:49.930
and wait for their claims
to be brought to them.

528
00:42:49.934 --> 00:42:53.433
- That is not my way.
- Does splitting firewood justify what's followed you here?

529
00:42:53.437 --> 00:42:55.468
Let it not be said
that Daemon Targaryen

530
00:42:55.472 --> 00:42:57.938
failed to dirty his
hands in this war.

531
00:42:57.942 --> 00:42:59.977
Oh. let me see them.

532
00:43:00.945 --> 00:43:02.909
- Sit.
- Ah.

533
00:43:02.913 --> 00:43:04.248
Sit!

534
00:43:07.685 --> 00:43:11.117
I hear strange things
from Bracken land.

535
00:43:11.121 --> 00:43:14.458
from Stone Hedge and
Lambswold and Mory.

536
00:43:15.326 --> 00:43:17.457
There's news. then?

537
00:43:17.461 --> 00:43:18.762
News?

538
00:43:19.897 --> 00:43:20.965
No.

539
00:43:22.967 --> 00:43:25.632
What I hear. I hear in the wind.

540
00:43:25.636 --> 00:43:28.939
Cries of anguish.

541
00:43:30.674 --> 00:43:32.706
Children being taken
from their mothers.

542
00:43:32.710 --> 00:43:36.710
men coming home to find
their doors unlatched...

543
00:43:36.714 --> 00:43:38.979
their wives carried away.

544
00:43:41.118 --> 00:43:43.883
War is a terrible thing.

545
00:43:43.887 --> 00:43:45.856
This is not war.

546
00:43:46.490 --> 00:43:49.089
These are crimes
against the innocent.

547
00:43:49.093 --> 00:43:51.257
that any upright
man would repudiate.

548
00:43:51.261 --> 00:43:53.994
Surely you haven't mistaken
me for an upright man.

549
00:43:55.866 --> 00:43:59.532
The Brackens had their
chance to do as I required.

550
00:43:59.536 --> 00:44:01.635
They will perhaps think
better of their decision

551
00:44:01.639 --> 00:44:05.175
if their children's
lives are staked on it.

552
00:44:06.243 --> 00:44:08.879
Is that the kind of
army you would raise?

553
00:44:09.780 --> 00:44:11.882
Men who hate you...

554
00:44:12.449 --> 00:44:14.014
who serve you under duress?

555
00:44:14.018 --> 00:44:17.250
Well. once they agree to serve
me. I'll treat them fairly.

556
00:44:17.254 --> 00:44:18.518
Set an example for the rest

557
00:44:18.522 --> 00:44:20.620
of the Riverlands to follow.

558
00:44:20.624 --> 00:44:23.023
And once again. in
the name of power.

559
00:44:23.027 --> 00:44:26.196
it's the weak and the
women who must endure.

560
00:44:28.766 --> 00:44:31.835
That fool. Aegon. is
unlike to survive.

561
00:44:33.704 --> 00:44:36.240
The realm will suffer
if Aemond One-Eye rules.

562
00:44:37.574 --> 00:44:39.209
You should pray
you never meet him.

563
00:44:39.710 --> 00:44:42.075
He will cut you down soon
as wish you good-day.

564
00:44:42.079 --> 00:44:43.677
I'd heard the same
thing about you.

565
00:44:43.681 --> 00:44:44.744
But I'll cross you no further.

566
00:44:44.748 --> 00:44:46.279
I'm sure your tactics
are. after all.

567
00:44:46.283 --> 00:44:48.181
approved by the queen.

568
00:44:53.724 --> 00:44:56.060
She cannot succeed. Alys.

569
00:44:56.593 --> 00:44:58.692
Even if I willed it to be so.

570
00:44:58.696 --> 00:45:00.894
The people who support her
will not be led by her.

571
00:45:00.898 --> 00:45:03.063
They look to a man for strength.

572
00:45:03.067 --> 00:45:04.130
Who's better suited to it?

573
00:45:04.134 --> 00:45:06.633
The Hightowers with
their scheming?

574
00:45:06.637 --> 00:45:09.073
Or Viserys's first true heir?

575
00:45:10.074 --> 00:45:12.439
When I take King's Landing...

576
00:45:12.443 --> 00:45:14.007
Rhaenyra is welcome
to join me there

577
00:45:14.011 --> 00:45:16.476
and take her place by my side.

578
00:45:16.480 --> 00:45:20.651
King and queen...
ruling together.

579
00:45:21.151 --> 00:45:23.850
- And if you lose?
- Then I'll be dead.

580
00:45:23.854 --> 00:45:26.119
and none of this
will be my problem.

581
00:45:26.123 --> 00:45:29.622
It's a pity. don't you think.
that you never knew your mother?

582
00:45:33.130 --> 00:45:35.466
A message. Your Grace.

583
00:45:37.067 --> 00:45:38.135
Uh...

584
00:45:40.370 --> 00:45:43.103
uh. fresh news from Stone Hedge.

585
00:45:43.107 --> 00:45:45.371
The Blackwoods have
overwhelmed the Brackens.

586
00:45:45.375 --> 00:45:48.979
and. uh. Lord Amos has
pledged his banner to you.

587
00:45:49.313 --> 00:45:51.682
House Bracken is yours.

588
00:45:52.816 --> 00:45:55.652
Call Ser Willem here so that
I might congratulate him.

589
00:45:55.986 --> 00:45:58.822
The Blackwoods will be
feted in these halls.

590
00:46:10.100 --> 00:46:12.136
I sought you at High Tide.

591
00:46:12.736 --> 00:46:15.305
I was surprised when
they said you were here.

592
00:46:16.306 --> 00:46:18.442
My castle is a tomb.

593
00:46:19.643 --> 00:46:21.912
Empty. Haunted.

594
00:46:22.579 --> 00:46:25.716
I am sad to have missed
its highest days.

595
00:46:26.583 --> 00:46:27.847
I imagine your Hall of Nine

596
00:46:27.851 --> 00:46:30.183
filled with lords and kings.

597
00:46:30.187 --> 00:46:33.557
all eager to treat with the
legendary Lord of the Tides.

598
00:46:35.292 --> 00:46:36.256
The wealth you brought back

599
00:46:36.260 --> 00:46:37.690
from Yi Ti and Asshai.

600
00:46:37.694 --> 00:46:41.131
inspiring awe and envy.

601
00:46:43.300 --> 00:46:45.569
I wonder if any of them
knew it was all for her.

602
00:46:54.478 --> 00:46:56.910
Queen Rhaenyra wishes
to name you Hand.

603
00:47:00.184 --> 00:47:04.254
Even the death of my wife
does not content her.

604
00:47:06.390 --> 00:47:08.725
Has she not asked
enough of my house?

605
00:47:09.126 --> 00:47:11.895
It is a sign of
her great esteem.

606
00:47:12.796 --> 00:47:14.961
Or does she think the
position will compensate me

607
00:47:14.965 --> 00:47:17.263
for my loss?

608
00:47:17.267 --> 00:47:19.666
Pledge your peace to
King's Landing. then.

609
00:47:19.670 --> 00:47:22.206
They will accept
it most gleefully.

610
00:47:24.575 --> 00:47:27.444
Rather I would sail into
the West and be lost.

611
00:47:28.478 --> 00:47:30.376
You have done so before.

612
00:47:30.380 --> 00:47:33.417
at great cost to yourself
and those who loved you.

613
00:47:35.752 --> 00:47:39.085
Rhaenys was not
only your wife...

614
00:47:39.089 --> 00:47:41.658
not a thing to be
taken from you.

615
00:47:42.326 --> 00:47:45.692
She was a Targaryen princess.

616
00:47:45.696 --> 00:47:46.960
The Queen Who Never Was.

617
00:47:46.964 --> 00:47:49.696
And she flew to Rook's
Rest of her own will.

618
00:47:49.700 --> 00:47:52.131
- In defense of her kin.
- And she died.

619
00:47:52.135 --> 00:47:54.471
She died as she would
have wished to die...

620
00:47:55.005 --> 00:47:58.108
with honor. in dragon fire.

621
00:47:58.575 --> 00:48:00.077
The way my mother chose...

622
00:48:02.145 --> 00:48:05.215
and the way I myself
wish to meet my end.

623
00:48:12.122 --> 00:48:15.388
I grieve my grandmother
who loved me

624
00:48:15.392 --> 00:48:17.794
but I carry her on with me.

625
00:48:18.829 --> 00:48:23.300
I will see Rhaenyra ascend the
Iron Throne. as Rhaenys wished.

626
00:48:23.800 --> 00:48:25.969
As Rhaenys herself should have.

627
00:48:28.572 --> 00:48:31.408
You yourself may
do as you see fit.

628
00:48:34.878 --> 00:48:36.509
Granddaughter.

629
00:48:43.921 --> 00:48:47.157
I would make you my heir.

630
00:48:48.625 --> 00:48:50.661
I am blood and fire.

631
00:48:51.128 --> 00:48:54.331
Driftmark must pass
to salt and sea.

632
00:49:13.016 --> 00:49:14.318
Your Grace.

633
00:49:17.854 --> 00:49:19.323
You were correct...

634
00:49:20.691 --> 00:49:23.560
in saying our best hope
of an army is with Daemon.

635
00:49:25.929 --> 00:49:31.668
And I have. perhaps. erred in
waiting for him to prove himself.

636
00:49:33.537 --> 00:49:35.706
I wish you to go to Harrenhal.

637
00:49:37.240 --> 00:49:39.876
Are you removing me
from your council?

638
00:49:41.311 --> 00:49:42.746
Ser Alfred...

639
00:49:43.513 --> 00:49:47.146
I-I-I will not deny you have
tried my patience of late.

640
00:49:47.150 --> 00:49:49.349
or that I would prefer a council

641
00:49:49.353 --> 00:49:51.050
more inclined to
champion their queen.

642
00:49:51.054 --> 00:49:53.653
but...

643
00:49:53.657 --> 00:49:56.990
you and your house
served my father well.

644
00:49:56.994 --> 00:50:00.364
and I know you will never
accept the Hightower claim.

645
00:50:01.798 --> 00:50:04.601
Not while I live. Your Grace.

646
00:50:07.170 --> 00:50:11.004
We cannot challenge King's
Landing without the Riverlands

647
00:50:11.008 --> 00:50:15.012
but I will not send a message by
raven for Daemon to disregard.

648
00:50:17.180 --> 00:50:23.182
I ask you to...
reason with him.

649
00:50:23.186 --> 00:50:28.125
Find out his state of
mind and his intentions.

650
00:50:29.926 --> 00:50:31.395
Intentions?

651
00:50:32.329 --> 00:50:36.033
Whether he means to raise a
host for me or for himself.

652
00:50:38.935 --> 00:50:40.133
He would not dare.

653
00:50:40.137 --> 00:50:43.140
Have you known Daemon
to lack in daring?

654
00:50:44.608 --> 00:50:46.239
Go now with haste.

655
00:50:46.243 --> 00:50:49.146
I'll send good men to
see to your safety.

656
00:50:56.586 --> 00:50:59.389
Have you any message for him?

657
00:51:03.060 --> 00:51:06.563
Tell him I would much like to
finish our last conversation.

658
00:51:08.965 --> 00:51:10.267
Your Grace.

659
00:51:46.503 --> 00:51:48.038
Your Grace.

660
00:51:51.575 --> 00:51:55.979
What is it. Ser Simon? Is
the pudding now served?

661
00:51:56.513 --> 00:51:58.945
The Riverlords have
come. Your Grace.

662
00:51:58.949 --> 00:52:01.918
- They wish an audience.
- Now?

663
00:52:02.385 --> 00:52:04.955
- What godless hour is it?
- The wolf.

664
00:52:05.555 --> 00:52:07.624
They are demanding
to speak presently.

665
00:52:38.388 --> 00:52:41.787
I see I must begin here
with a lesson in etiquette.

666
00:52:41.791 --> 00:52:43.055
Or failing that. in proper fear

667
00:52:43.059 --> 00:52:45.262
of your Targaryen master.

668
00:52:46.763 --> 00:52:51.268
Is there some reason you feel
free to wake a king in his bed?

669
00:52:51.968 --> 00:52:54.534
Or shall I now begin
your education?

670
00:52:54.538 --> 00:52:55.935
House Bracken

671
00:52:55.939 --> 00:52:59.805
have been brought to heel at
the hands of Willem Blackwood.

672
00:52:59.809 --> 00:53:03.109
- That news is stale.
- Yes.

673
00:53:03.113 --> 00:53:05.077
There have been.
um. complications.

674
00:53:05.081 --> 00:53:07.580
The sacred septs
on Bracken lands

675
00:53:07.584 --> 00:53:11.017
- were looted and burned.
- As were the fields and farms.

676
00:53:11.021 --> 00:53:12.585
The livestock was stolen

677
00:53:12.589 --> 00:53:14.086
and our peasants
put to the sword.

678
00:53:14.090 --> 00:53:16.789
They pursued the women
and the children.

679
00:53:16.793 --> 00:53:18.191
There were works of barbarity.

680
00:53:18.195 --> 00:53:22.128
Punishing Bracken for his own
treasons is one thing. aye.

681
00:53:22.132 --> 00:53:24.897
- But these other acts.
- The Brackens were given their chance.

682
00:53:24.901 --> 00:53:27.433
- They would not see reason.
- The Blackwoods have exploited

683
00:53:27.437 --> 00:53:29.302
the war for the crown
to visit atrocities

684
00:53:29.306 --> 00:53:31.938
- upon their old rivals.
- I have seen my fair share of their quarrels.

685
00:53:31.942 --> 00:53:33.406
and I tell you. there
is no honor in a fight

686
00:53:33.410 --> 00:53:35.508
- such as this.
- Honor? What of common decency?

687
00:53:35.512 --> 00:53:37.777
These beasts proudly carried

688
00:53:37.781 --> 00:53:39.645
the banner of House Targaryen.

689
00:53:39.649 --> 00:53:41.751
Red dragon on black.

690
00:53:48.024 --> 00:53:51.561
A terrible war is being
fought in these lands.

691
00:53:54.864 --> 00:53:57.067
Have you looked after our girls?

692
00:54:04.341 --> 00:54:06.405
We should've expected
nothing more from a man

693
00:54:06.409 --> 00:54:08.541
who ordered the
slaughter of a child

694
00:54:08.545 --> 00:54:10.180
in his mother's arms.

695
00:54:12.115 --> 00:54:15.414
That is a lie. And I will have the
man who told it brought before me.

696
00:54:15.418 --> 00:54:20.357
Well. your man is half
the kingdom. my prince.

697
00:54:23.193 --> 00:54:25.262
Know this. interloper:

698
00:54:25.829 --> 00:54:28.594
the Riverlands are
an ancient place.

699
00:54:28.598 --> 00:54:32.335
watched closely by the
eyes of old gods and new.

700
00:54:32.736 --> 00:54:34.433
And dragon or no.

701
00:54:34.437 --> 00:54:37.974
we shall not raise our
banners for a tyrant.

702
00:55:45.608 --> 00:55:49.846
- Move along. lass.
- I have an errand... for the lady Mysaria.

703
00:55:50.947 --> 00:55:52.248
I thought she was dead.

704
00:55:52.982 --> 00:55:55.418
Would she die without
collecting her due?

705
00:55:56.953 --> 00:55:58.922
I must see an old friend.

706
00:56:00.490 --> 00:56:02.692
Most people want out these days.

707
00:56:47.904 --> 00:56:48.834
Elinda.

708
00:57:40.657 --> 00:57:42.826
Was it worth the price?

709
00:58:33.776 --> 00:58:35.512
{\an8}Mummy.

710
00:58:52.529 --> 00:58:54.097
Prince Jacaerys. Your Grace.

711
00:59:18.821 --> 00:59:20.156
Visenya.

712
00:59:20.957 --> 00:59:26.729
Vhagar's first rider. and the
first wielder of Dark Sister.

713
00:59:28.264 --> 00:59:30.729
I hope you do not mean
to use her as an example.

714
00:59:30.733 --> 00:59:32.331
Why shouldn't I?

715
00:59:32.335 --> 00:59:34.737
W... It was a long time ago.

716
00:59:44.847 --> 00:59:47.250
What is the mood at the Twins?

717
00:59:48.718 --> 00:59:51.087
Did his lordship quibble?

718
00:59:53.323 --> 00:59:57.193
He wishes for the Freys
to be granted Harrenhal.

719
00:59:58.561 --> 01:00:00.930
At war's end. Assuming.

720
01:00:03.566 --> 01:00:05.230
I'm proud of you. Jace.

721
01:00:05.234 --> 01:00:07.704
You have done our
cause a great service.

722
01:00:10.073 --> 01:00:12.976
Then. why do you look angry?

723
01:00:21.084 --> 01:00:24.083
You chafed at being
prevented from action.

724
01:00:24.087 --> 01:00:26.885
Imagine my lot. I'm a
dragon rider as well.

725
01:00:26.889 --> 01:00:29.959
with a war being fought
over my ascension.

726
01:00:30.994 --> 01:00:33.162
And yet. I must wait here...

727
01:00:33.997 --> 01:00:36.362
always prudent...

728
01:00:36.366 --> 01:00:37.830
sending others to fight

729
01:00:37.834 --> 01:00:40.136
and be felled in my name.

730
01:00:40.570 --> 01:00:42.905
Even you have managed
to do your part.

731
01:00:43.439 --> 01:00:45.274
You are the queen...

732
01:00:45.708 --> 01:00:46.905
the tie that binds us.

733
01:00:46.909 --> 01:00:48.607
- No harm can come to you.
- And you are my son.

734
01:00:48.611 --> 01:00:50.880
and I did not give
you leave to go.

735
01:00:52.782 --> 01:00:55.518
You do not give me
leave to go to anything.

736
01:00:55.852 --> 01:00:57.149
But who else is there?
Rhaenys is dead.

737
01:00:57.153 --> 01:00:58.984
and Baela cannot bear
the burden alone.

738
01:00:58.988 --> 01:01:01.654
And when Aemond comes
hunting for you?

739
01:01:01.658 --> 01:01:03.989
Your dragon is young.

740
01:01:03.993 --> 01:01:06.262
Will you fly before
Vhagar as Luke did?

741
01:01:13.102 --> 01:01:15.071
Perhaps Daemon could...

742
01:01:18.474 --> 01:01:20.376
Daemon is not here.

743
01:01:21.077 --> 01:01:24.710
And Aemond now rules
in King's Landing.

744
01:01:24.714 --> 01:01:28.814
- Is Aegon dead?
- Dead or alive. we have no answer for Vhagar.

745
01:01:28.818 --> 01:01:32.422
Aemond will not wait long to press
his advantage. And then what?

746
01:01:34.757 --> 01:01:36.422
I have done all I can from here.

747
01:01:36.426 --> 01:01:39.425
sent my messages.
invoked my alliances.

748
01:01:39.429 --> 01:01:41.898
But if all else fails.
it is I who must fight.

749
01:01:43.599 --> 01:01:46.432
Vhagar is big. but
Syrax is quicker.

750
01:01:46.436 --> 01:01:51.274
- So was Meleys.
- Meleys fought two dragons and one of them is slain.

751
01:01:52.742 --> 01:01:54.039
Shall I fight for my birthright?

752
01:01:54.043 --> 01:01:56.979
Or shall I wait here until
we are all destroyed?

753
01:02:02.719 --> 01:02:04.754
I need dragons.

754
01:02:08.057 --> 01:02:11.060
We have no dearth of dragons.

755
01:02:11.761 --> 01:02:14.860
We have two large enough
to stand against Vhagar.

756
01:02:14.864 --> 01:02:18.230
They are called
Vermithor and Silverwing

757
01:02:18.234 --> 01:02:19.732
and they sleep just
beneath our feet.

758
01:02:19.736 --> 01:02:20.999
Yes. and if only
they had riders.

759
01:02:21.003 --> 01:02:23.106
none could stand against me.

760
01:02:23.706 --> 01:02:27.176
I would go forth in strength
and not from necessity.

761
01:02:28.444 --> 01:02:29.675
There is Rhaena.

762
01:02:29.679 --> 01:02:33.015
Who nearly lost her life
in her last attempt.

763
01:02:34.383 --> 01:02:36.519
I would not risk it again.

764
01:02:42.225 --> 01:02:45.394
There are those of our
line who never ruled.

765
01:02:46.095 --> 01:02:49.561
Those who married into
other noble houses.

766
01:02:49.565 --> 01:02:52.397
their children born
with other names.

767
01:02:52.401 --> 01:02:56.168
A generation ago. or more.
Their blood would be thin.

768
01:02:56.172 --> 01:02:57.673
And yet...

769
01:02:58.775 --> 01:03:02.941
A dragon will only accept
a dragon lord to ride it.

770
01:03:02.945 --> 01:03:07.112
- Or so say the histories.
- Valyrian histories.

771
01:03:07.116 --> 01:03:09.114
Written to gild us in glory.

772
01:03:11.888 --> 01:03:14.657
Are you suggesting we put
a Mallister on a dragon?

773
01:03:15.124 --> 01:03:18.828
- A Tarly?
- It's better than death and defeat.

774
01:03:24.600 --> 01:03:28.133
There are records here.
surely. of our line

775
01:03:28.137 --> 01:03:30.435
and of those who fell out of it.

776
01:03:37.880 --> 01:03:39.611
There could be scores of them.

777
01:03:47.223 --> 01:03:49.192
It's a mad thought.
